cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.DM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper is about linear logic and its complexity properties. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper studies the complexity of linear logic proof-nets and characterizes polynomial time. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the proofs-as-programs correspondence. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper deals with complexity classes and proposes semantic criteria based on context semantics.
